column1: 1. Index crimes are classified as crime against person and property. These are also considered focus crimes

2. Non-index crimes include all reckless imprudence resulting (RIR) resulting to homicide, physical 
    injury and damage to property incidents, as reported to police. Further, violation of special laws 
    and other non-index crimes are also included.
3. New indicator in Public satety indicator added
Source: Philippine National Police, Crime Information Reporting and Analysis System (CIRAS)
